### Why the pick beat the others

Justice's brief explicitly names VEGF×PD-L1, JAK ADCs, and trispecific TCEs as core interests, plus broad biotech/pharma headlines. The EVOKE-03 halt is a major Phase 3 readout that (a) is a TROP-2 ADC + PD-1 combo failure — directly in the ADC + IO wheelhouse, (b) lets us draw the explicit line to ivonescimab's HARMONi-6 win (PD-1×VEGF bispecific reshaping 1L NSCLC), and (c) raises the bar for datopotamab deruxtecan + Imfinzi and pumitamig — the next reads in this setting. AZD0120 was the strongest bioRxiv option but is preclinical preprint signal; the EVOKE-03 halt is a market-moving Phase 3 outcome that hits Justice's audience harder.
